//! Pneuma TTS acoustic model (Pneuma TTS, Channel α).
//!
//! Reference: arXiv 2106.06103 (VITS — Conditional Variational Autoencoder
//! with Adversarial Learning for End-to-End Text-to-Speech, Kim et al. 2021).
//! https://arxiv.org/abs/2106.06103
//! Voice weights: rhasspy/piper (https://github.com/rhasspy/piper).
//!
//! Consumes a stream of phoneme IDs (output of a G2P front-end such as eSpeak)
//! and produces a row-major mel-spectrogram of shape (`n_mels=80`, `n_frames`)
//! that the Pneuma vocoder ([`crate::model_pneuma_tts_vocoder`], built by
//! Channel β) consumes to synthesise PCM audio.
//!
//! Pipeline (Piper-class VITS small, encoder-only flavour):
//!   1. Phoneme embedding: `tts_phoneme_embed.weight[phonemes]` -> (seq, hidden)
//!   2. Add sinusoidal positional embedding (computed on the fly; no tensor)
//!   3. N x { pre-LN, multi-head self-attention (no causal mask), residual,
//!            pre-LN, MLP (fc1 -> GELU -> fc2), residual }
//!   4. Duration predictor — for v1 a constant 4-frame stub (see TODO below)
//!   5. Length regulator — repeat each phoneme embedding `dur_t` times
//!   6. Mel projection — linear (n_mels, hidden) per expanded frame
//!
//! Mirrors [`crate::model_whisper_encoder::WhisperEncoder`] structurally:
//! - Tensor names are pre-resolved at [`TtsAcousticModel::new`] so the hot
//!   path never `format!`s.
//! - Per-utterance scratch buffers are reused across forward passes; only the
//!   final expanded mel buffer is allocated per call (its length is
//!   utterance-dependent).
//! - All weight bytes are fetched lazily through [`WeightBackend`] so the same
//!   model object works against mmap, HTTP-range, or wasm-host weight sources.
//!
//! v1 stubs (intentional, called out for the Phase 3 follow-on):
//! - **Duration predictor** is a hard-coded 4 mel frames per phoneme. A real
//!   VITS uses a stochastic duration predictor with a normalising flow; weights
//!   `tts_dur_predictor_*` exist in the tensor table but are *not* consumed by
//!   v1. Phase 3 wires them in.
//! - **Speaker embedding / style vector** is unused (single-speaker v1).
//! - **Flow-based decoder** between encoder and mel projection is collapsed
//!   into a plain linear projection. Phase 3 introduces the Glow-class flow.

